text: Khachemzy () is a rural locality (an aul) in Dmitriyevskoye Rural Settlement of Koshekhablsky District, Adygea, Russia. The population was 672 as of 2018. There are 16 streets. == Geography == The aul is located on the left bank of the Fars River, 6 km west from Druzhba and 17 km north-west from Koshekhabl. == Ethnicity == The settlement is inhabited by Adighes. == References == Category:Rural localities in Koshekhablsky District
title: Khachemzy
